New Records: The Dodgers clinched their 11th NL West division title in 12 years
Key Match Events: Will Smith hit the game-tying home run
Shohei Ohtani singled in the go-ahead run
Mookie Betts delivered a two-run single
Andy Pages belted a two-run home run
Pre-Game Insights: The Dodgers took the final two games of the series to win the division crown
Manager Dave Roberts emphasized the importance of overcoming adversity
Post-Match Reflections: Manager Dave Roberts expressed pride in the team's resilience
Will Smith mentioned that his game-tying homer 'got everyone going'
Miscellaneous Highlights: Freddie Freeman left the game with a right ankle injury
The Dodgers will look to sew up the best record in the NL and the number one overall seed as they head to Colorado for the final series of the regular season
Others: The game was played at Dodger Stadium
The Dodgers' victory clinched a first-round bye in the postseason
